CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 20, 1957, pg. 28 reads: "Don't Believe in Signs - These motorists, including the one sitting in automobile beneath the "NO PARKING AT ANY TIME" sign, just don't believe in such warnings, apparently. Two such signs, plus one for a street car stop, are clearly visible in this block between Dinwiddie and Green Sts., diagonally across the street from the Centre Ave. Police Station.  Yet, car and truck drivers ignore them daily.  Some park, then go on Downtown, thus saving parking lot charges...- Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Centre Avenue between Dinwiddie and Green Streets, with Thorofare Market, Roma Bottling Works billboard, and sign for West View Park, Hill District
